== F.4 — Year-Level Competency Markers

The primary competency test for each year, plus the secondary markers that confirm readiness to transition to the next tier.

=== Year One — Tyro Tier

*Primary test:* Production of a Procedurally Complete Plant Stone.

A Procedurally Complete Plant Stone demonstrates:
+ Triple separation — the student can evidence the separation of Mercury (essence), Sulphur (aromatic fraction), and Salt (calcined ash) from the same plant
+ Cohobation completed at least once — the calcined salt has been moistened with liquid essence and digested under gentle warmth until the liquid clears
+ Diagnostic test passed — the preparation, when gently warmed, exhibits the characteristic wax-like flow described in the tradition; it is not dry, brittle, or inert

